Want to get involved with our coffee events?
-
Every thing that we do as the UK chapter of the @specialtycoffeeassociation is from our passion of coffee, our enjoyment to meet and socialise with likeminded people and to spread the knowledge of speciality coffee. That being said we couldn’t do it without the help of all our volunteers on every aspect of what we do. We are looking for volunteers to help with the upcoming #UKBC2020 finals on 27th & 28th February in Brighton and the #UKCiGS202 & #UKBRC2020 finals on 3rd to 5th March in London. If you want to get involved, please email info@scauk.coffee

Repost from aeropress - This week’s  2019 World AeroPress Championship in numbers:⠀
⠀
More than *3,500* hopeful brewers⠀
*160+* national and regional competitions across *65* countries, resulting in *65* national champions⠀
*800* spectators at the global final at @ovalspace, London on Sunday 24th November⠀
… but there will only be *ONE* winner. Come and join us as we find out winner and celebrate a whole world of AeroPressing talent.

Again this year we have chosen to use the amazing @Umeshiso_ rainbow cupping spoons throughout the #UKCTC2020 championship and also on the trophies produced by @paradox_design_coffee. We chose these spoons because the project aligns so closely to the SCA UK’s beliefs. This is what Umeko said about the Rainbow Spoon Project: “The Rainbow Spoon Project is about empowering marginalized folks in the coffee community. When I first started cupping, I was so intimidated, I was afraid to actually say anything about the coffees. And I think a lot of people feel that way, even after working in coffee for a while - particularly folks who hold marginalized identities. 
So for me, the rainbow spoon disarms something (cupping) that used to scare me, and still sometimes does. And it's a reminder that everyone has a place at the cupping table.” Thank you Umeko 🙌🏻🌈☕️🥄 #UKCTC2020 #SCAUK #Specialtycoffee #baristas #espresso #cupping #cuptasters #CupTastersChampionship
